      "writtenOn": "2020-11-24T00:13:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just a few questions here:\n\n* Do we know whether this formula is equivalent to Wang\u0027s when w\u003d\u003d1 all throughout?\n* Would it be faster to either compute this value separately for rational quadratics, or else take advantage of the fact that w0\u003d\u003dw3\u003d\u003d1 and w1\u003d\u003dw2?\n* If going this route, we will also need to update GrWangsFormula on the CPU side and handle conics separately\n* You mentioned some cases where running wang\u0027s on the down-projected points wasn\u0027t sufficient. Do you know what these conics are and what their w values are?",
      "revId": "00b83bd2f31e5b1a339995d4a3fc47d0faa01cd1",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
