      "writtenOn": "2020-11-24T14:13:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It seems to be a heuristic at best unfortunately. The goal is to minimize r \u003d max_i{length(P_i)}, meaning even with subtracting the center point C, you can always come up with an adversarial curve with a control point super far away, growing r arbitrarily.\n\nOnce we have some time to understand the original Wang\u0027s formula more deeply, I\u0027m curious if we\u0027ll discover a similar \"vulnerability\" to far-away control points.\n\nAnyway, we could certainly try your midpoint idea, or perhaps a median instead of averaging.",
